142.8	Gesamtkunstwerk	Gesamtkunstwerk	A Gesamtkunstwerk (translated as total work of art, ideal work of art, universal artwork, synthesis of the arts, comprehensive artwork, all-embracing art form, or total artwork) is a work of art that makes use of all or many art forms or strives to do so. The term is a German word which has come to be accepted in English as a term in aesthetics.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b7/RobieHouseWindows_ChicagoIL.jpg/220px-RobieHouseWindows_ChicagoIL.jpg
